# Lessons Learned

## AI Agents Benefit From Individual Identities

Providing agents with dedicated accounts preserves:

* Accountability
* Audit trails
* Permission boundaries
* Operational clarity

Agent actions can now be clearly distinguished from administrator actions.

---

## Observation Before Authority

Read-only access provided substantial value without administrative privileges.

Most useful operational tasks involved:

* Observation
* Analysis
* Reporting
* Documentation

rather than direct modification of systems.

---

## Knowledge Systems Amplify Agent Utility

Mira became significantly more useful once granted access to:

* Infrastructure documentation
* Live system information
* Memos
* BookStack

The combination of documentation and observation proved more valuable than either capability alone.

---

## Agent Specialization Emerged Naturally

Distinct operational roles began to develop:

### Mira

* Infrastructure observation
* Documentation
* Reporting
* Knowledge management

### Hermes

* Development
* Automation
* Local experimentation
* Technical troubleshooting

This specialization reduced complexity while improving effectiveness.

